NVRAM_Initialise

Description:
This function initialises the NVRAM Api

psBlock : The SPI Master device to use.

pui8ScratchBuffer : An application specified buffer address for the NVRAM API to use internally. This buffer should be at least as large as the greatest device block size.

ui32ScratchSize : The size of the working buffer.

NVRAM_eResult : Either NVRAM_SUCCESS or NVRAM_FAILURE

NVRAM_ReadBlock

Description:
This function reads a block from device memory.

ui32Address : The block address to read the data from.

NVRAM_eResult : Either NVRAM_SUCCESS or NVRAM_FAILURE

FILE* NVRAM_fopen ( NVRAM_sDevice *  psDevice,
NVRAM_sFile *  psFileHandle,
IMG_UINT32  ui32NVRAMAddress 
)

NVRAM_fopen

Description:
Allows sequential reads from a starting point in NVRAM, as if reading from a file. Using this method will prevent unnecessary NVRAM accesses when reading multiple small amounts of data - a copy of the last page read is kept locally to prevent multiple NVRAM reads where multiple read accesses are being made from the same NVRAM page.

psDevice : The target device to operate on.

psFileHandle : The address of a user owned 'NVRAM_sFile' structure which the API can use to keep track of this 'file read'.

ui32NVRAMAddress : The NVRAM address at which the 'file' starts.

FILE * : The function returns a file pointer which must be provided in subsequent references to this 'file read'.

size_t  ui32Count,

NVRAM_fread

Description:
This function reads data from NVRAM into a provided buffer.

pvBuffer : The target buffer.

ui32Size : The size of the unit to read.

ui32Count : The number of units to read.

pFileHandle : A file handle returned when 'NVRAM_fopen' was called.

IMG_INT32 : The number of bytes read.

NVRAM_fclose

Description:
This function closes a file previously opened with 'NVRAM_fopen'.
